com.payvment.continuuity
Class ClusterWriterFlow

java.lang.Object
  com.payvment.continuuity.ClusterWriterFlow
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.continuuity.api.flow.Flow
public class ClusterWriterFlow
extends Object
implements com.continuuity.api.flow.Flow

Flow application used to process clusters of categories. These clusters are used as an input to activity and popular feed queries. A mapping from a clusterid to a set of weighted categories is stored.

Activity and popular feeds are on a per-category basis, so to support cluster queries, the clusters are queried and a query is made on each category in the cluster and aggregated.

Flow Design

Input

The input to this Flow is a stream named clusters which contains cluster events in the following CSV format:

      clusterid,category,weight
or when doing a reset, in the format:
      reset_clusters,max_cluster_id,"msg"

Flowlets

This Flow is made up of three Flowlets.

The first flowlet, ClusterWriterFlow.ClusterSourceParser, is responsible for parsing the cluster CSV line into the internal tuple representation and determining whether the operation is a WRITE or RESET. The Flowlet will then send the Tuple to either the ClusterWriter or ClusterReset Flowlets. See CLUSTER_PARSER_TO_WRITER_SCHEMA and CLUSTER_PARSER_TO_RESET_SCHEMA for tuple schemas.

The Tuple is then passed on to one of the remaining two Flowlets, ClusterWriterFlow.ClusterWriter and ClusterWriterFlow.ClusterReset, where a cluster entry is written or all entries are cleared.

See the javadoc of each Flowlet class for more detailed information.

Tables

This Flow utilizes one Tables.

clusterTable is an instance of a ClusterTable used to store cluster information, a mapping from cluster id to categories and weights. The primary key on this table is clusterId.
